Copper sulphate (CuSO4) reacts with NaOH solution in the reaction to form copper hydroxide Cu(OH)2. Then ascorbic acid as surfactant was added into copper hydroxide solution leading to the formation of copper oxides (Cu2O)38. In the last step, Cu2O powder was heated in NH3 atmosphere, which reacts with Cu2O to form Cu3N. The reaction mechanism for the formation of Cu2O and Cu3N is given below:52CuSO4+2NaOH→2CuOH+2NaSO4,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
